Alice is clearly trying to establish a sense of urgency and scarcity by mentioning a backup buyer.  While she might have someone else interested, there's no reason to believe you can't negotiate a better price.  You have a guaranteed option with John at $1,000,000, so you don't lose anything by rejecting Alice's initial offer and seeing if she'll come down in price.
